main event: A series of sightings and reports related to unidentified flying objects (UFOs) documented in Project 10073 and Project Blue Book during February 1961.
interesting points: Possible meteor sighting indicated in the Project 10073 record, Multiple sightings of astrological phenomena misidentified as UFOs reported across various locations such as Tioga and St. Louis, A military report noted fine targets moving at high speeds around Washington, D.C., Observers reported a multi-colored UFO with family witnessed sighting in Lakeport, California, A case from Lakeville, Massachusetts described a yellow elongated UFO with a burning odor.
sighted object: Various unidentified flying objects including a possible meteor and a multi-colored UFO
location: Various locations including Lakeport, California and Lakeville, Massachusetts, USA
witness description: Witnesses include military personnel, civilians, and family members
